{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781957287119,"sessionID":"ses_11b11fa04ffedi2ibaUFk2XYdN","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"449441167","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Cache API\n\nA simple in-memory cache implementation using a Map for storing and retrieving values.\n\n## createCache()\n\nCreates a new cache instance with `get`, `set`, `delete`, and `clear` methods.\n\n```js\nimport { createCache } from './cache'\nconst cache = createCache()\n```\n\n## Methods\n\n### get(key)\n\nRetrieves the value associated with the given `key`.\n\n```js\nimport { createCache } from './cache'\nconst cache = createCache()\n\nconst value = cache.get('my-key')\n```\n\nReturns the cached value or `undefined` if the key does not exist.\n\n### set(key, value)\n\nStores the given `value` under the specified `key`.\n\n```js\nimport { createCache } from './cache'\nconst cache = createCache()\n\ncache.set('my-key', 'my-value')\n```\n\nReturns the cached value.\n\n### delete(key)\n\nRemoves the entry with the specified `key` from the cache.\n\n```js\nimport { createCache } from './cache'\nconst cache = createCache()\n\ncache.delete('my-key')\n```\n\nReturns the deleted value or `undefined` if the key does not exist.\n\n### clear()\n\nRemoves all entries from the cache.\n\n```js\nimport { createCache } from './cache'\nconst cache = createCache()\n\ncache.clear()\n```\n\n## Implementation Details\n\nThe cache uses a native `Map` under the hood for storing key-value pairs. The cache instance is returned as an object with the four methods attached, allowing for easy usage without managing a separate object reference.","filePath":"/private/tmp/tokenwarden-bench/2026-06-20T06-38-17-288Z/tokenwarden-docs-from-code-2/repo/bench-artifacts/cache-api.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/private/tmp/tokenwarden-bench/2026-06-20T06-38-17-288Z/tokenwarden-docs-from-code-2/repo/bench-artifacts/cache-api.md","exists":false,"trunc